The failure was a real repo bug, and it’s fixed now on `origin/main`.

What was wrong: the Alembic config inside Docker always used `backend/alembic.ini`’s `localhost:5432`, so when you ran migration commands in the backend container it tried to connect to the container itself instead of the `postgres` service. I fixed Alembic to honor `ARGUS_DB_URL`, added a regression test, and updated the lab guide with the exact schema-repair step.

Pushed commit: `fa23889`  
Message: `fix: honor ARGUS_DB_URL in alembic`

Run this now on your iMac:

```bash
cd "$HOME/vision"
git pull --rebase origin main

docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.dev.yml exec backend \
  /tmp/argus-backend-venv/bin/alembic upgrade head

docker exec infra-postgres-1 psql -U argus -d argus -c '\dt'
docker exec infra-postgres-1 psql -U argus -d argus -c 'select * from alembic_version;'
```

What you want to see:
- `models` appears in `\dt`
- `alembic_version` shows `0003_prompt11_quota`

Then get a fresh token and confirm the models route is healthy again:

```bash
TOKEN="$(
  curl -sS \
    --data 'grant_type=password&client_id=argus-cli&username=admin-dev&password=argus-admin-pass' \
    http://127.0.0.1:8080/realms/argus-dev/protocol/openid-connect/token |
  python3 -c 'import json,sys; print(json.load(sys.stdin)["access_token"])'
)"

curl -sS \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/models | python3 -m json.tool
```

I verified the fix locally with:
- `python3 -m uv run pytest tests/migrations/test_alembic_config.py tests/core/test_config.py` → `4 passed`

